### Tested versions

- Reproducible in Godot 4.4.1.stable.mono

### System information

MXLinux - Godot v4.4.1.stable.mono - Debian GNU/Linux 12 (bookworm) 12 on X11 - X11 display driver, Multi-window, 1 monitor - OpenGL 3 (Compatibility) - AMD Radeon R4 Graphics (stoney, LLVM 15.0.6, DRM 3.49, 6.1.0-33-amd64) - AMD A6-9225 RADEON R4, 5 COMPUTE CORES 2C+3G (2 threads) 

### Issue description

### What I expected
 I expected the _customNodeScene to be properly instantiated  and not null when accessing it (after casting).

### What actually happened?
The _customNodeScene variable is null  in the editor mode, causing a null reference error when attempting to call CustomPrint.

## Codes

``` cs

using Godot;
using System;

[Tool]
public partial class MainScene : Node2D
{
    bool _print=false;
    [Export] bool Print
    {get=>_print;
    set{
        // Error: _customNodeScene IS null here.(Everytime)
        _customNodeScene.CustomPrint("Hey, this is working int the Editor Mode.");
        }
    }
    CustomNodeScene _customNodeScene;

    public override void _Ready()
    {		
        var packedScene = GD.Load<PackedScene>("res://src/CustomNode/custom_node.tscn");
        var instance = packedScene.Instantiate();
        AddChild(instance);
        instance.Owner=GetTree().EditedSceneRoot;

        _customNodeScene=instance as CustomNodeScene;

        if(!Engine.IsEditorHint())
        {
            // _customNodeScene is NOT null here.
            _customNodeScene.CustomPrint("Hey, this is working in play/run.");
        }
        else
        {
            // Error: _customNodeScene IS null here.
            _customNodeScene.CustomPrint("Hey, this is working int the Editor Mode.");
        }
    }
}

/// CustomNode
using Godot;
using System;

public partial class CustomNodeScene : Node2D
{
    public void CustomPrint(string text)
    {
        GD.Print(text);
    }
}

```
##### "Scene" suffix on the class names indicates that the script is attached to a scene root in the editor.

### Project file structure
<img width="192" height="211" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/20bfd4be-0671-4a45-b9e0-b285ce8e9051" />

### Error message on accessing _customNodeScene in the editor mode.
```
  ERROR: /root/godot/modules/mono/glue/GodotSharp/GodotSharp/Core/NativeInterop/ExceptionUtils.cs:113 - System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object.
  ERROR:    at MainScene.set_Print(Boolean value) in /home/Sobhan/Documents/Projects/CastingToCustomNodeIssue/src/Main/MainScene.cs:line 9
  ERROR:    at MainScene.SetGodotClassPropertyValue(godot_string_name& name, godot_variant& value) in /home/Sobhan/Documents/Projects/CastingToCustomNodeIssue/.godot/mono/temp/obj/Debug/Godot.SourceGenerators/Godot.SourceGenerators.ScriptPropertiesGenerator/MainScene_ScriptProperties.generated.cs:line 29
  ERROR:    at Godot.Bridge.CSharpInstanceBridge.Set(IntPtr godotObjectGCHandle, godot_string_name* name, godot_variant* value) in /root/godot/modules/mono/glue/GodotSharp/GodotSharp/Core/Bridge/CSharpInstanceBridge.cs:line 57
```

### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a new project in Godot.
2. Add a custom node scene and attach a script with the provided code to it (like CustomNode shown).
3. Add a tool script to another Node2D scene (like the MainScene shown).
5. Open the inspector and toggle the Print boolean in the editor. Or just build the project while the scene is opened on the editor.
6. Observe the null reference error when trying to call CustomPrint.

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

[CastingToCustomNodeIssue.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/23164242/CastingToCustomNodeIssue.zip)

### Tested versions

* Reproducible in v4.5.1.stable.mono
* Older versions not tested

### System information

Windows 11 - Godot v4.5.1.stable.mono - Compatibility

### Issue description

I tried to create an async extension of HttpRequest but it simply does not show up in the global class hierarchy:
```csharp
[GlobalClass]
public partial class AsyncHttpRequest : HttpRequest
{
    [Export] public string BaseAddressLink { get; set; } = "";

    [Signal] public delegate void RequestFinishedEventHandler();

    private bool _isRequesting;

    public async Task<HttpResult> RequestAsync(string endpoint,
        string[] customHeaders = null,
        HttpClient.Method method = HttpClient.Method.Get,
        string requestData = "")
    {
        if (_isRequesting)
            return HttpResult.FromError(Error.Busy);

        _isRequesting = true;
        try
        {
            var error = Request($"{BaseAddressLink}/{endpoint}", customHeaders, method, requestData);
            if (error != Error.Ok) return HttpResult.FromError(error);

            var args = await ToSignal(this, HttpRequest.SignalName.RequestCompleted);
            EmitSignalRequestFinished();
            return HttpResult.FromSynchronousRequest(args);
        }
        finally
        {
            _isRequesting = false;
        }
    }
}
```

### Steps to reproduce

- Create a new script
- Extend HttpRequest
- Annotate as GlobalClass
- Build
- Check "add new node" menu

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

I do not think it is necessary for this. It is a small bug that is probably well known (and maybe even an intenional feature).
